Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Bair's spokesman Andrew Gray =
declined to
comment. Obama's transition spokeswoman Stephanie Cutter had no =
immediate
comment. </span></font><font color=3Dblue><span =
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Obama Plan </span></font><font =
color=3Dblue><span
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Even if Bair remains at the FDIC, =
the
Obama economic team has decided that she won't play a central role in =
policy,
the people said. While Bair, like Obama, has favored aid for <st1:Street =
w:st=3D"on"><st1:address
 w:st=3D"on">Main Street</st1:address></st1:Street> as well as Wall =
Street, the
new administration will have its own plan to help the millions of people =
facing
eviction from their homes. It will also have its own team to run the
government's $700 billion bailout program, they added. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Pushing out the head of the FDIC, =
which
oversees more than 5,000 banks and savings institutions, would clash =
with the
pledges made by Obama's own transition team. Bair has become the most =
prominent
Republican regulator, and the incoming administration has promised to =
give
Republicans important jobs. </span></font><font color=3Dblue><span
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>&#8220;You'll see Republicans =
again, in
his administration, not just a token member in the Cabinet, but you'll =
see them
spread throughout the administration,&#8221; transition director John =
Podesta
said in an interview with Bloomberg Television last week. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Frank Proposal =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Bair, who was appointed by =
President
George W. Bush to a term as chairman that ends in 2011, has been =
lobbying
behind the scenes for a stepped-up role in the Obama administration. =
Frank, a
Massachusetts Democrat, has suggested that she be named to a special =
post to
oversee government-wide programs to stop foreclosures. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Bair &#8220;brings a lot of
credibility&#8221; on crafting ideas to ease the mortgage crisis, said =
Kevin
Petrasic, a former Office of Thrift Supervision official who now works =
at law
firm Paul, Hastings, Janofsky &amp; Walker in <st1:State =
w:st=3D"on"><st1:place
 w:st=3D"on">Washington</st1:place></st1:State>. </span></font><font =
color=3Dblue><span
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>In public comments, Bair, 54, has
indicated she'd like to stay on, while she'd be prepared to depart if =
Obama
wants someone else to take the helm at the FDIC. </span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>She said at a press conference in =
<st1:State
w:st=3D"on"><st1:place w:st=3D"on">Washington</st1:place></st1:State> =
Nov. 25 she'd
work &#8220;in whatever role they want me in this institution to =
play.&#8221;
The month before, Bair said in an interview on &#8220;Political Capital =
with Al
Hunt&#8221; on Bloomberg Television that &#8220;I'm happy to go back to
academia too. So I want to be flexible for the next president.&#8221; =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Protecting Fund =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Geithner became increasingly wary =
of Bair
as she worked with the other regulatory agencies on emergency bailouts =
of banks
in recent months. The <st1:State w:st=3D"on"><st1:place w:st=3D"on">New =
York</st1:place></st1:State>
fed chief has been concerned that Bair was more worried about keeping =
the
FDIC's insurance program protected than she was about the entire =
financial
system, one person said. </span></font><font color=3Dblue><span =
style=3D'color:
blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Bair twice sparred with her =
colleagues at
the Fed and Treasury over efforts involving Citigroup. In October, she
acquiesced to Wachovia Corp.'s agreement to a takeover by Wells Fargo =
&amp; Co.
days after agreeing to back an initial deal with Citigroup. Geithner was
concerned that allowing the Citigroup transaction to fail would inhibit =
other
lenders from working with the FDIC on any subsequent rescues, the people =
said. </span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Wells Fargo offered about $15 =
billion for
Wachovia, compared with Citigroup's $2.2 billion deal to acquire =
Wachovia's
banking operations, and didn't need any FDIC aid. </span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Citigroup Crisis =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Citigroup's position weakened, =
with its
shares losing as much as 65 percent after the failed Wachovia deal amid =
a
collapse in investor confidence -- precipitating another rescue attempt. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Again, Bair held out for =
concessions as
the Fed and Treasury sought to shield Citigroup from losses in its =
holdings of
toxic assets. Bair insisted on getting preferred shares for the FDIC in =
the New
York-based bank. She also demanded that Citigroup agree to implement =
mortgage
modifications according to a model developed by her agency. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>At one point during a Nov. 23 Fed =
board
meeting about the Citigroup rescue, Chairman Ben S. Bernanke stepped out =
to
take a call from Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson. Returning a few =
moments
later, Bernanke told his colleagues that the secretary was still locked =
in
negotiations with Bair, whose demands were delaying the deal. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>The political peril of ousting a =
popular
regulator who has sided with struggling homeowners and sought tougher
conditions on financial firms could fuel charges that Geithner and other =
Obama
appointees are too closely connected to Wall Street. </span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>'Willing to Stand Up' =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>&#8220;I don't think you want an =
FDIC
chairman who isn't willing to stand up,&#8221; former FDIC Chairman =
William
Isaac, who is now head of Secura Group LLC in <st1:place =
w:st=3D"on"><st1:City
 w:st=3D"on">Falls Church</st1:City>, <st1:State =
w:st=3D"on">Virginia</st1:State></st1:place>,
said in an interview. </span></font><font color=3Dblue><span =
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>On other issues, too, Bair has =
stepped out
in front of her Bush administration colleagues. </span></font><font =
color=3Dblue><span
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>As the mortgage bust deepened, =
Bair
repeatedly pushed Fed and Treasury officials to boost aid for =
homeowners. </span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>In 2007, Bair told lawmakers the =
Fed
should use its authority over home-loan standards to tighten oversight =
and
crack down on the practices that contributed to the subprime mortgage =
mess. </span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>This year, Bair has proposed =
using
taxpayer funds to help refinance loans for struggling homeowners. She =
told
legislators at an Oct. 23 hearing that the Treasury could use its $700 =
billion
financial-rescue fund to set terms for mortgage modifications and offer
guarantees for loans that meet the standards. </span></font><font =
color=3Dblue><span
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>Senators pressed Neel Kashkari, =
the
Treasury official overseeing the Troubled Asset Relief Program, on his
department's reaction. &#8220;We are looking very hard&#8221; on the =
proposal,
he said. </span></font><font color=3Dblue><span =
style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>The White House later that month =
sought to
scale back Bair's idea to use as much as $50 billion from the program.
Yesterday, an official said Paulson instead is considering a proposal to =
drive
down home-loan rates through purchases of mortgage-backed securities. =
</span></font><font
color=3Dblue><span style=3D'color:blue'><o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblue face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:blue'>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>=


<p class=3DMsoNormal><font size=3D3 color=3Dblack face=3D"Times New =
Roman"><span
style=3D'font-size:12.0pt;color:black'>To contact the reporter on this =
story:
Robert Schmidt in <st1:State w:st=3D"on"><st1:place =
w:st=3D"on">Washington</st1:place></st1:State>
